<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-813-584  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 813 584.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  August 6, 1990 v5 n106 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Reorganization: TEL Electronics announces sales reorganization.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tel Electronics Inc. (management).andO;Ticker:    TELS.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationSales ManagementTelephone SystemsCommunications EquipmentStrategic Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>REORGANIZATION: TEL ELECTRONICS ANNOUNCES SALES REORGANIZATIONandM;American Fork UT based TEL electronics Inc. has a new national sales forcethat is nearly double its previous size.andM;It has only been a month since the reorganization and already sales areshowing improvement.andM;&quot;We're committed to increased sales and we're not afraid to make changes,&quot;said Tracy Tolbert, vice president of sales.andP;  &quot;We took our existing salesforce and brought in outside talent specifically trained in technical sales.&quot;andO;Not only did TEL increase their sales force, but they took a unique approachand instituted team selling.andM;TEL's sales approach combines two sales people into one team.andP;  One advantageis that twice the chance of a personality match between buyer and seller nowexists.andP;  In addition, this approach provides better service for the customer.andO;If one sales person is out of the office, there will still be a partneravailable who is familiar with the buyer and his account.andM;In the past, each sales person was responsible for various states throughoutthe United States.andP;  An individual could have Texas and at the same time haveMaine.andP;  Under the new sales program, the United States is divided into salesregions such as the Northwest or Southeast.andP;  This new program allows a salesteam to become familiar with a region's culture and habits which enable theteam to better sell to their buyers.andM;One of the biggest advantages of this approach is that it promotes team workand produces synergy within a sales team whose members were selected for thespecific talents they bring to that team.andM;According to Mark Phillips, co-manager of regional sales over the WesternRegion, &quot;In areas in which I am weak, my sales partner has strengths.andP;  Thesum of both our talents increases our sales.&quot; Not only have sales increased,but the number of new dealers signed a month has also increased.andP;  CurrentlyTEL signs 15-20 dealers each month, and under the new plan, by the end of1990 TEL should be signing between 35-40 dealers monthly.andM;TEL electronics inc. designs, produces, and markets microprocessor-basedtelephone call accounting, telephone management, line scanners, voice/mailprocessing systems, automated attendants and other telecommunicationssystems.andP;  All of TEL's products are designed and produced in the UnitedStates.andO;</TEXT></DOC>